41 /*!
42  * \class CEmptyMap
43  * \brief We use this dummy class instead of std::map when
44  * we only need the enum definition and not the string to
45  * enum maps, this makes compilation much faster.
46  */
47 template <typename T, typename U>
48 struct CEmptyMap {
49  CEmptyMap(std::initializer_list<std::pair<const T, U> >) {}
50 };

156 /*!
157  * \brief Get the number of faces of the element.
158  * \param[in] elementType - element type
159  * \return number of faces
160  */
161 inline unsigned short nFacesOfElementType(unsigned short elementType) {
162  switch (elementType) {
163  case LINE: return N_FACES_LINE;
164  case TRIANGLE: return N_FACES_TRIANGLE;
165  case QUADRILATERAL: return N_FACES_QUADRILATERAL;
166  case TETRAHEDRON: return N_FACES_TETRAHEDRON;
167  case HEXAHEDRON: return N_FACES_HEXAHEDRON;
168  case PYRAMID: return N_FACES_PYRAMID;
169  case PRISM: return N_FACES_PRISM;
170  default: assert(false && "Invalid element type."); return 0;
171  }
172 }
173 
174 /*!
175  * \brief Get the number of points of the element.
176  * \param[in] elementType - element type
177  * \return number of points
178  */
179 inline unsigned short nPointsOfElementType(unsigned short elementType) {
180  switch (elementType) {
181  case LINE: return N_POINTS_LINE;
182  case TRIANGLE: return N_POINTS_TRIANGLE;
183  case QUADRILATERAL: return N_POINTS_QUADRILATERAL;
184  case TETRAHEDRON: return N_POINTS_TETRAHEDRON;
185  case HEXAHEDRON: return N_POINTS_HEXAHEDRON;
186  case PYRAMID: return N_POINTS_PYRAMID;
187  case PRISM: return N_POINTS_PRISM;
188  default: assert(false && "Invalid element type."); return 0;
189  }
190 }

1028 /*!
1029  * \brief Function to parse SST options.
1030  * \param[in] SST_Options - Selected SST option from config.
1031  * \param[in] nSST_Options - Number of options selected.
1032  * \param[in] rank - MPI rank.
1033  * \return Struct with SST options.
1034  */
1035 inline SST_ParsedOptions ParseSSTOptions(const SST_OPTIONS *SST_Options, unsigned short nSST_Options, int rank) {
1036  SST_ParsedOptions SSTParsedOptions;
1037 
1038  auto IsPresent = [&](SST_OPTIONS option) {
1039  const auto sst_options_end = SST_Options + nSST_Options;
1040  return std::find(SST_Options, sst_options_end, option) != sst_options_end;
1041  };
1042 
1043  const bool found_1994 = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V1994);
1044  const bool found_2003 = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V2003);
1045  const bool found_1994m = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V1994m);
1046  const bool found_2003m = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V2003m);
1047 
1048  const bool default_version = !found_1994 && !found_1994m && !found_2003 && !found_2003m;
1049 
1050  const bool sst_1994 = found_1994 || found_1994m;
1051  /*--- Default version since v8. ---*/
1052  const bool sst_2003 = found_2003 || found_2003m || default_version;
1053 
1054  /*--- When V2003m or V1994m is selected, we automatically select sst_m. ---*/
1055  const bool sst_m = found_1994m || found_2003m || default_version;
1056 
1057  const bool sst_sust = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::SUST);
1058  const bool sst_v = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::V);
1059  const bool sst_kl = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::KL);
1060  const bool sst_uq = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::UQ);
1061  const bool sst_compWilcox = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::COMP_Wilcox);
1062  const bool sst_compSarkar = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::COMP_Sarkar);
1063  const bool sst_dll = IsPresent(SST_OPTIONS::DLL);
1064 
1065  if (sst_1994 && sst_2003) {
1066  SU2_MPI::Error("Two versions (1994 and 2003) selected for SST_OPTIONS. Please choose only one.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1067  } else if (sst_2003) {
1068  SSTParsedOptions.version = SST_OPTIONS::V2003;
1069  } else {
1070  SSTParsedOptions.version = SST_OPTIONS::V1994;
1071  }
1072 
1073  // Parse production modifications
1074  if ((int(sst_v) + int(sst_kl) + int(sst_uq)) > 1) {
1075  SU2_MPI::Error("Please select only one SST production term modifier (VORTICITY, KATO-LAUNDER, or UQ).", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1076  } else if (sst_v) {
1077  SSTParsedOptions.production = SST_OPTIONS::V;
1078  } else if (sst_kl) {
1079  SSTParsedOptions.production = SST_OPTIONS::KL;
1080  } else if (sst_uq) {
1081  SSTParsedOptions.production = SST_OPTIONS::UQ;
1082  }
1083 
1084  // Parse compressibility options
1085  if (sst_compWilcox && sst_compSarkar) {
1086  SU2_MPI::Error("Please select only one compressibility correction (COMPRESSIBILITY-WILCOX or COMPRESSIBILITY-SARKAR).", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1087  } else if (sst_compWilcox) {
1088  SSTParsedOptions.production = SST_OPTIONS::COMP_Wilcox;
1089  } else if (sst_compSarkar) {
1090  SSTParsedOptions.production = SST_OPTIONS::COMP_Sarkar;
1091  }
1092 
1093  SSTParsedOptions.sust = sst_sust;
1094  SSTParsedOptions.modified = sst_m;
1095  SSTParsedOptions.uq = sst_uq;
1096  SSTParsedOptions.compWilcox = sst_compWilcox;
1097  SSTParsedOptions.compSarkar = sst_compSarkar;
1098  SSTParsedOptions.dll = sst_dll;
1099 
1100  return SSTParsedOptions;
1101 }

1141 /*!
1142  * \brief Function to parse SA options.
1143  * \param[in] SA_Options - Selected SA option from config.
1144  * \param[in] nSA_Options - Number of options selected.
1145  * \param[in] rank - MPI rank.
1146  * \return Struct with SA options.
1147  */
1148 inline SA_ParsedOptions ParseSAOptions(const SA_OPTIONS *SA_Options, unsigned short nSA_Options, int rank) {
1149  SA_ParsedOptions SAParsedOptions;
1150 
1151  auto IsPresent = [&](SA_OPTIONS option) {
1152  const auto sa_options_end = SA_Options + nSA_Options;
1153  return std::find(SA_Options, sa_options_end, option) != sa_options_end;
1154  };
1155 
1156  const bool found_neg = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::NEG);
1157  const bool found_edw = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::EDW);
1158  const bool found_bsl = !found_neg && !found_edw;
1159 
1160  if (found_neg && found_edw) {
1161  SU2_MPI::Error("Two versions (Negative and Edwards) selected for SA_OPTIONS. Please choose only one.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1162  }
1163 
1164  if (found_bsl) {
1165  SAParsedOptions.version = SA_OPTIONS::NONE;
1166  } else if (found_neg) {
1167  SAParsedOptions.version = SA_OPTIONS::NEG;
1168  } else {
1169  SAParsedOptions.version = SA_OPTIONS::EDW;
1170  }
1171  SAParsedOptions.ft2 = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::FT2);
1172  SAParsedOptions.qcr2000 = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::QCR2000);
1173  SAParsedOptions.comp = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::COMP);
1174  SAParsedOptions.rot = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::ROT);
1175  SAParsedOptions.bc = IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::BC);
1176 
1177  /*--- Validate user settings when not in experimental mode. ---*/
1178  if (!IsPresent(SA_OPTIONS::EXP)) {
1179  const bool any_but_bc = SAParsedOptions.ft2 || SAParsedOptions.qcr2000 || SAParsedOptions.comp || SAParsedOptions.rot;
1180 
1181  switch (SAParsedOptions.version) {
1182  case SA_OPTIONS::NEG:
1183  if (!SAParsedOptions.ft2 || SAParsedOptions.bc)
1184  SU2_MPI::Error("A non-standard version of SA-neg was requested (see https://turbmodels.larc.nasa.gov/spalart.html).\n"
1185  "If you want to continue, add EXPERIMENTAL to SA_OPTIONS.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1186  break;
1187  case SA_OPTIONS::EDW:
1188  if (any_but_bc || SAParsedOptions.bc)
1189  SU2_MPI::Error("A non-standard version of SA-noft2-Edwards was requested (see https://turbmodels.larc.nasa.gov/spalart.html).\n"
1190  "If you want to continue, add EXPERIMENTAL to SA_OPTIONS.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1191  break;
1192  default:
1193  if (SAParsedOptions.bc && any_but_bc)
1194  SU2_MPI::Error("A non-standard version of SA-BCM was requested (see https://turbmodels.larc.nasa.gov/spalart.html).\n"
1195  "If you want to continue, add EXPERIMENTAL to SA_OPTIONS.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1196  break;
1197  }
1198  }
1199  return SAParsedOptions;
1200 }

1265 /*!

1267  * \param[in] LM_Options - Selected LM option from config.
1268  * \param[in] nLM_Options - Number of options selected.
1269  * \param[in] rank - MPI rank.
1270  * \return Struct with SA options.
1271  */
1272 inline LM_ParsedOptions ParseLMOptions(const LM_OPTIONS *LM_Options, unsigned short nLM_Options, int rank, TURB_MODEL Kind_Turb_Model) {
1273  LM_ParsedOptions LMParsedOptions;
1274 
1275  auto IsPresent = [&](LM_OPTIONS option) {
1276  const auto lm_options_end = LM_Options + nLM_Options;
1277  return std::find(LM_Options, lm_options_end, option) != lm_options_end;
1278  };
1279 
1280  LMParsedOptions.LM2015 = IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::LM2015);
1281 
1282  int NFoundCorrelations = 0;
1283  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::MALAN)) {
1284  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MALAN;
1285  NFoundCorrelations++;
1286  }
1287  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::SULUKSNA)) {
1288  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::SULUKSNA;
1289  NFoundCorrelations++;
1290  }
1291  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::KRAUSE)) {
1292  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::KRAUSE;
1293  NFoundCorrelations++;
1294  }
1295  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::KRAUSE_HYPER)) {
1296  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::KRAUSE_HYPER;
1297  NFoundCorrelations++;
1298  }
1299  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::MEDIDA_BAEDER)) {
1300  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MEDIDA_BAEDER;
1301  NFoundCorrelations++;
1302  }
1303  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::MEDIDA)) {
1304  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MEDIDA;
1305  NFoundCorrelations++;
1306  }
1307  if (IsPresent(LM_OPTIONS::MENTER_LANGTRY)) {
1308  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MENTER_LANGTRY;
1309  NFoundCorrelations++;
1310  }
1311 
1312  if (NFoundCorrelations > 1) {
1313  SU2_MPI::Error("Two correlations selected for LM_OPTIONS. Please choose only one.", CURRENT_FUNCTION);
1314  }
1315 
1316  if (LMParsedOptions.Correlation == TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::DEFAULT){
1317  if (Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::SST) {
1318  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MENTER_LANGTRY;
1319  } else if (Kind_Turb_Model == TURB_MODEL::SA) {
1320  LMParsedOptions.Correlation = TURB_TRANS_CORRELATION::MALAN;
1321  }
1322  }
1323 
1324  return LMParsedOptions;
1325 }
